  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your wok or frying pan over high heat. Add olive oil.",
    "Slice the scallions into thin strips, and finely chop the garlic cloves.",
    "Add kidneys to the hot pan, cover with a lid, and cook for about 10 minutes until golden brown on all sides.",
    "In another bowl, mix together soy sauce, mirin, water, oyster sauce, ginger, sugar, salt, and pepper. Stir well.",
    "Pour the marinade over the kidneys in the pan, reduce heat to medium-low, cover with a lid again, and let cook for about 10 more minutes until all liquid is absorbed.",
    "Garnish with chopped scallions before serving."
